@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

   @{b}Introduction@{ub}
  --------------

   Execute64 is a usefull tool for all C64 owner. You don“t need to store
   your programs on slow 1541 disks any longer.

   Just load a little tool on your C64. (like the good  old  "Ultra-Load")
   By  using a special @{"Cable" link "CABLE"} your software will be transfered direct info
   the c64 memory. The loading procedure takes only a few seconds.
@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

   @{b}System requirements@{ub}
  ---------------------

   Execute64 (should work) works on all Amigas with OS 2.0 or higher.

   If you want to use compressed files in conjunction with the XPK system,
   then it is requiered to install xpk. (-8

   Of cource you need to @{"connect" link "Cable"} your Amiga and your C64!

   That`s all!
@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Features"

   @{b}Features@{ub}
  -----------

 ° 100% Assembler

 ° supports Bin, P00, SID, T64 and D64 without any external tools.

 ° XPK support! (Allows to store the C64 files in compressed form)

 ° Auto start (@{"You are able to disable the autorun" link "PT_NoStart"})

 ° A brilliant C64 music player (I did it again!)

 ° File selection via ASL and or Shell/Workbench!

 ° It is possible to load programs from $400 to $ffff into the C64 memory.
   This  allows  to  load frezzed programs without using the special Modul
   (e.G. Action Replay) loader. (The IO space is  disabled  during  memory
   access.)

 ° @{"Load" link "PT_BASE"} and @{"run adresse" link "PT_SYS"} may be specified, without patching  the  original
   C64.

 ° It“s possible to define the run address within the @{"file name" link "FAQRUN"}. So it is
   not  required  to  patch  the  file  or  switch of @{"auto run" link "PT_NOSTART"} for manual
   startup.

@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

